On Fri, 7 May 1999, Victor STANESCU wrote:
> I made a patch for the 2.2.7 kernel which sets the permissions for the
> /proc/<pid> and files inside so users can read information about only
> their processes. If someone will try "ps aux" he will see a list
> composed only by the processes he owns, and no other.
Your patch works a treat. I trust that it will go into 2.3.x ASAP. I am
not prepared to let users loose on my machine without that patch. 
